    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A juicy edible fruit of the tropical American bromeliad, Ananas comosus. The large multiple fruit develops from a conical spike of flowers; it has yellow flesh surrounded by a tough segmented skin and is topped by a tuft of stiff spiky leaves.</Note_Text>
